you can lock your screen with the shortcut
ctrl+alt (or option in the apple keyboard) + l

you have to go to 'Screen Locking'
DO NOT look for Screen Locking in the menu bar

just open 'System setting' and from there navigate to the Screen Locking section
otherwise you will not see the wallpapers and it will not work

therefore got to
System Setting-> Desktop Behaviour-> Screen Locking
click on the tab 'Appearance' and select your preferred wallpaper
click ok

DONE!
